WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:12.541 --> 00:14.042
<i>Carmen?</i>

00:17.346 --> 00:19.047
Oh,<i> mon dieu,</i>
you look <i> magnifique.</i>

00:19.148 --> 00:20.428
Thanks.

00:20.483 --> 00:22.851
I'm going on a talk show
to promote my new album,

00:22.952 --> 00:24.219
and I can't decide
what to wear.

00:24.320 --> 00:25.720
Wear this.

00:25.821 --> 00:27.722
<i>Mon coeur,</i>
what happened to our plan?

00:27.823 --> 00:29.424
You were supposed to
seduce Jacklyn.

00:29.525 --> 00:32.726
I know. I couldn't go
through with it.

00:32.828 --> 00:34.162
She's been nothing
but nice to me.

00:34.263 --> 00:36.064
Is that why you haven't
returned any of my calls?

00:36.165 --> 00:37.699
No, I lost my stupid phone.

00:37.800 --> 00:39.334
Oh, I thought you were
mad at me.

00:39.435 --> 00:41.302
Where was the last place
you had it?

00:41.404 --> 00:43.004
- If I knew, it wouldn't be lost.
- Oh, let's see.

00:43.105 --> 00:46.274
The last text you sent was...

00:46.375 --> 00:48.076
when you were with Jacklyn.

00:48.177 --> 00:51.179
Oh, my God. I left my phone
at your house!

00:51.280 --> 00:54.049
It's okay.
I'll go home and find it.

00:54.150 --> 00:56.051
What if she already did?

00:59.321 --> 01:02.123
- Thank you, Thomas.
- Is everything okay?

01:04.427 --> 01:05.894
Remember when I said

01:05.995 --> 01:07.962
I thought my husband
was having an affair?

01:08.064 --> 01:12.901
Well, I finally know
who he's been screwing.

01:13.002 --> 01:15.737
And the bitch is gonna pay.

01:19.809 --> 01:22.811
<b>- sync and corrections by Zac -
- www.addic7ed.com -</b>

01:30.396 --> 01:31.630
Oh, there you are.

01:31.731 --> 01:34.700
Mr. Michael came to take
Katy for the weekend

01:34.801 --> 01:36.401
and she couldn't find
her dolly.

01:36.502 --> 01:38.470
It's in my car.
Uh, I'll get it to her.

01:38.571 --> 01:41.039
- She was very upset.
- Oh.

01:41.140 --> 01:43.442
I tried calling you,
but you didn't answer.

01:43.543 --> 01:46.445
Sorry, I was, uh, at the gym.

01:46.546 --> 01:49.715
And I had my...
phone turned off.

01:49.816 --> 01:53.018
You've been going to
the gym a lot lately.

01:53.119 --> 01:54.486
Every afternoon.

01:54.587 --> 01:56.455
Yes, since the separation,

01:56.556 --> 01:59.358
the... exercise has helped
clear my head.

01:59.459 --> 02:01.660
I have
a really great... trainer.

02:01.761 --> 02:03.161
That's good.

02:03.262 --> 02:06.031
Anyway, uh,
I'm gonna take a shower.

02:06.132 --> 02:08.265
Oh, wait.
I'm doing laundry.

02:08.368 --> 02:10.088
You want me to throw in
your gym clothes?

02:10.136 --> 02:11.536
Where is your bag?

02:11.637 --> 02:13.672
I must've left it at the gym!

02:13.773 --> 02:16.675
It's okay.
I'll call the gym for you.

02:16.776 --> 02:18.176
Which one is it?

02:18.277 --> 02:21.179
You know what?
I don't wanna trouble you.

02:21.280 --> 02:22.714
I'll call them myself.

02:26.753 --> 02:31.056
Uh, sorry to interrupt.
Carmen Luna to see you...

02:31.157 --> 02:32.557
without an appointment.

02:32.658 --> 02:35.027
You know,
it's not a good time, Carmen.

02:35.128 --> 02:38.563
I just wanted to ask you if
I left my phone at your house.

02:40.767 --> 02:42.234
You did.

02:42.335 --> 02:45.470
Yeah, I found it
between the sofa cushions.

02:45.571 --> 02:49.408
Thank God! I've been looking
for this everywhere.

02:49.509 --> 02:50.642
Did your husband call me?

02:50.743 --> 02:52.463
I'm sure he's been trying
to reach me.

02:52.478 --> 02:53.945
Excuse me?

02:54.047 --> 02:56.081
Why would Sebastien be
trying to reach you?

02:56.182 --> 02:58.316
Oh, he's my realtor.

02:58.418 --> 03:00.252
He didn't tell you?

03:00.353 --> 03:02.154
So...

03:02.255 --> 03:04.589
Let me get this straight.

03:04.690 --> 03:07.125
Out of all the realtors
in town,

03:07.226 --> 03:08.560
you chose my husband?

03:08.661 --> 03:10.095
Mm-hmm. I wanna buy a condo.

03:10.196 --> 03:12.264
And you told me that
he was in real estate.

03:12.365 --> 03:13.698
So I thought you'd be happy.

03:15.134 --> 03:16.334
Was that wrong?

03:24.410 --> 03:28.080
I am... so relieved.

03:28.181 --> 03:30.415
I mean, you... wow.

03:30.516 --> 03:34.219
You wouldn't <i> believe</i>
what's been going on in my mind.

03:34.320 --> 03:38.490
I...you're so...
Such a beautiful woman and...

03:38.591 --> 03:40.525
Sebastien is...

03:40.626 --> 03:42.746
Wait, you... you thought
I would... with your husband?

03:42.795 --> 03:45.530
No, no, I know.
I know, it's so stupid!

03:45.631 --> 03:47.999
I mean, I was gonna murder you.

03:48.101 --> 03:50.101
I'm glad you didn't.

03:50.136 --> 03:53.505
Oh, I'm so sorry.
I assumed the worst.

03:53.606 --> 03:55.373
Can you forgive me?

03:55.475 --> 03:57.175
Oh, don't be ridiculous.
Of course I forgive you.

03:57.276 --> 03:58.556
Oh! Thank you.

04:00.179 --> 04:02.414
Ah! Well...

04:02.515 --> 04:06.251
Now that that's out of
my system,

04:06.352 --> 04:08.286
let's grab some coffee

04:08.387 --> 04:11.957
so we can chat about
your big TV debut.

04:19.265 --> 04:20.464
Hi.

04:20.565 --> 04:22.467
I didn't know what
the traditional gift was

04:22.568 --> 04:24.903
for accusing of
your boyfriend of murder,

04:25.004 --> 04:26.304
so I went with a plant.

04:26.405 --> 04:27.672
Don't kill it.

04:27.773 --> 04:29.207
Seriously?

04:29.308 --> 04:30.442
Oh, come on.

04:30.543 --> 04:32.144
We're gonna laugh
about this someday.

04:32.245 --> 04:33.645
Not today.

04:33.746 --> 04:38.150
Jesse... I can't tell you
how sorry I am.

04:38.251 --> 04:42.554
I...I just think I'm so used
to picking bad guys

04:42.655 --> 04:45.590
that I didn't trust
when I finally had a good one.

04:45.691 --> 04:50.328
- Look, I don't wanna be mad.
- Then don't be.

04:50.429 --> 04:52.430
But that doesn't mean I can just
pick up where we left off.

04:52.532 --> 04:56.034
You need time. I get it,
but... please, I just...

04:56.135 --> 04:58.737
I don't wanna lose you
from my life.

05:01.641 --> 05:03.175
Can I ask you a favor?

05:03.276 --> 05:05.143
Yes, anything.

05:05.244 --> 05:10.348
I still really need a job,
and I have this one lead.

05:10.449 --> 05:12.317
I was hoping you would
give me a reference.

05:12.418 --> 05:17.656
Of course! I'll give you
a killer recommendation.

05:17.757 --> 05:19.391
Not that <i> you're</i> a killer.

05:20.693 --> 05:22.994
I think I'm gonna go now.

05:24.297 --> 05:28.466
Yes, Genevieve, I'm taking
great care of Dr. Neff.

05:28.568 --> 05:32.537
Trust me, I will win him over
before you come home.

05:32.638 --> 05:36.374
Kiss the kids for me.

05:36.475 --> 05:39.511
Mrs. Delatour having fun
in New York with Remi and...

05:39.612 --> 05:41.279
Valentina.

05:41.380 --> 05:44.449
Does Dr. Neff like mayo
or mustard on his sandwich?

05:44.550 --> 05:46.084
Dijon mustard.

05:46.185 --> 05:48.505
He and I got off
to a rocky start.

05:48.521 --> 05:53.692
I am trying to impress him.
Got any tips for me?

05:53.793 --> 05:57.262
Well...
you could smile more.

05:57.363 --> 06:00.265
Smile more?

06:01.467 --> 06:04.869
I guess I could do that.

06:04.971 --> 06:07.252
You know, Dr. Neff is so happy
with Mrs. Delatour.

06:07.340 --> 06:09.874
I don't think I've seen him
love him anyone this much

06:09.976 --> 06:13.178
since... Lurlene passed.

06:13.279 --> 06:15.647
Lurlene?
Which wife was she?

06:15.748 --> 06:17.249
Lurlene was his mother.

06:17.350 --> 06:20.085
He loved her more than
anyone in the world.

06:20.186 --> 06:23.421
That... sounds healthy.

06:23.522 --> 06:26.258
Dr. Neff,
I made you lunch.

06:26.359 --> 06:30.028
Genevieve says turkey
is your favorite.

06:30.129 --> 06:33.098
Well, that's very considerate.
Actually, turkey <i> is</i> my favorite.

06:33.199 --> 06:36.034
Oh, well, then you'll really
like what I'm making for dinner.

06:41.741 --> 06:45.644
That looks positively
succulent.

06:45.745 --> 06:47.212
Wonderful effort, Zoila,

06:47.313 --> 06:51.783
but I don't want to spoil
my appetite.

06:54.654 --> 06:57.589
<i>Dios mio, se√±or.</i>

06:57.690 --> 06:59.424
I just mopped this floor
last week.

06:59.525 --> 07:01.893
What? You only mop in here
once a week?

07:01.994 --> 07:03.495
The point is,
that little boy of yours

07:03.596 --> 07:05.997
- makes a very big mess.
- He's not my little boy.

07:06.098 --> 07:08.867
He's just the crazy pet project
of my bored, deluded wi...

07:08.968 --> 07:10.535
Well, hello there, dear.

07:10.636 --> 07:12.937
Adrian, I have
some appointments tomorrow.

07:13.039 --> 07:15.440
I will be gone all day.
I need you to watch Deion.

07:15.541 --> 07:17.676
Oh, I'm sure Carmen
can babysit.

07:20.680 --> 07:22.314
This isn't about Carmen.

07:22.415 --> 07:25.250
This is about you
bonding with our child.

07:25.351 --> 07:27.352
As lovely as that sounds,
I'm extremely busy tomorrow.

07:27.453 --> 07:28.887
With what? Golf?

07:28.988 --> 07:30.388
And also a nap.

07:30.489 --> 07:32.624
Just take Deion along
to the club.

07:32.725 --> 07:34.292
He'll love the fresh air.

07:34.393 --> 07:37.429
Need I remind you,
I didn't want the b-o-y

07:37.530 --> 07:39.030
in the first place.

07:39.131 --> 07:40.265
I can spell, you know.

07:40.366 --> 07:41.966
This is not a negotiation.

07:42.068 --> 07:44.028
You're going to spend the day
with our little boy,

07:44.036 --> 07:47.794
and that's that.

07:50.899 --> 07:52.432
What's so funny?

07:52.534 --> 07:54.201
You're her bitch.

07:57.231 --> 08:00.825
Mr. Michael thinks Mrs. Taylor's
having an affair?

08:00.832 --> 08:01.965
Mm-hmm.

08:02.066 --> 08:04.334
I bet the affair's
with her trainer.

08:04.336 --> 08:06.103
- What?
- Every day, Mrs. Taylor says

08:06.204 --> 08:07.771
she's going to the gym,

08:07.872 --> 08:10.140
but I don't think
she's exercising.

08:10.241 --> 08:11.408
That's ridiculous.

08:11.509 --> 08:13.911
Taylor is not sleeping
with her trainer.

08:14.012 --> 08:16.380
Well, she's having an affair
with somebody.

08:16.481 --> 08:17.948
How would you even know that?

08:18.049 --> 08:19.750
Because she's the maid.

08:19.851 --> 08:21.418
If a spouse is cheating,
we're always the first to know.

08:21.519 --> 08:23.220
Not <i> always.</i>

08:23.321 --> 08:25.522
When Genevieve's fourth husband
was cheating on her, I knew.

08:25.623 --> 08:27.858
And when she was cheating
on him, I knew that, too.

08:27.959 --> 08:29.493
- They were both cheating?
- Nobody ever slept at home.

08:29.594 --> 08:33.030
I never had to make the bed.
That was a great marriage.

08:34.631 --> 08:36.366
If Mr. Michael said the affair's
been going on for months,

08:36.467 --> 08:39.269
then maybe Blanca knew
about it, too.

08:39.370 --> 08:41.871
Wait. At Zoila's wedding,
Blanca told me

08:41.972 --> 08:44.408
there was something going on
at that house.

08:44.509 --> 08:45.943
And you're just telling us now?

08:46.044 --> 08:48.345
What? I was mad.
She took my dress!

08:48.446 --> 08:51.982
And let's not forget,
it's still out there somewhere.

08:52.083 --> 08:54.518
Yes, Blanca's dead,
but that's the big mystery.

08:54.619 --> 08:55.986
#Where'sCarmen'sdress?

08:56.087 --> 08:58.489
Maybe Mrs. Taylor
was asking Blanca

08:58.590 --> 09:00.491
to keep her affair a secret.

09:00.592 --> 09:03.494
But Blanca had a big mouth,
so Taylor took her out.

09:03.595 --> 09:06.296
No, Taylor didn't do it.

09:06.397 --> 09:07.965
Whoever killed Louie
killed Blanca.

09:08.066 --> 09:09.466
And to chop up a body,

09:09.567 --> 09:11.268
the killer would have
to be strong.

09:11.369 --> 09:13.403
- Someone in really good shape.
- Like a trainer?

09:13.505 --> 09:16.840
I'm just saying.

09:16.941 --> 09:20.244
If Mrs. Taylor is
not the killer,

09:20.345 --> 09:22.946
then maybe her lover is.

09:27.218 --> 09:30.020
Hello. Oh, is Lorraine in?
I have an appointment.

09:30.121 --> 09:31.889
Oh, you must be Mrs. Powell.

09:31.890 --> 09:34.042
I'm Natalie,
your new case worker.

09:34.198 --> 09:36.799
Oh.
What happened to Lorraine?

09:36.800 --> 09:38.801
Lorraine's job is
to place children.

09:38.902 --> 09:41.671
My job is to determine
if that placement is working.

09:41.772 --> 09:44.607
Well, it is lovely to meet you.

09:44.708 --> 09:47.910
May I add, I simply adore
that blazer.

09:48.012 --> 09:49.379
Is it polyester?

09:49.480 --> 09:52.615
Lorraine may have fallen for that
kind of sweet talk, but not me.

09:52.716 --> 09:54.836
I need to conduct a home visit
and confirm

09:54.918 --> 09:57.186
Deion's living conditions
are satisfactory.

09:57.287 --> 10:00.256
Oh, his living conditions
are more than satisfactory.

10:00.357 --> 10:02.258
I don't like to use
the word "mansion,"

10:02.359 --> 10:03.960
but it's a mansion.

10:04.061 --> 10:06.763
Well, the size of your home
is irrelevant.

10:06.864 --> 10:09.732
You might feel differently
if you saw it by helicopter.

10:09.833 --> 10:11.734
Now I see there hasn't been
an interview

10:11.835 --> 10:13.236
with Mr. Powell yet.

10:13.337 --> 10:15.571
I believe Lorraine
handled that.

10:15.673 --> 10:17.940
So you can just check
that little box.

10:18.042 --> 10:19.308
I don't cut corners,

10:19.410 --> 10:21.811
not when the welfare
of a child is at stake.

10:21.912 --> 10:23.312
I'll be there
tomorrow at 3:00.

10:23.414 --> 10:25.114
Make sure your husband
is present.

10:25.215 --> 10:26.315
Of course.

10:26.417 --> 10:29.652
He'll be so excited.

10:33.223 --> 10:34.691
This is boring.

10:34.792 --> 10:36.292
Well, we should be
playing golf.

10:36.393 --> 10:39.028
But somebody took so long
finding his shoes this morning

10:39.129 --> 10:40.263
that I missed my tee time.

10:40.364 --> 10:41.831
I want chocolate milk.

10:41.932 --> 10:44.267
It's a country club.
They don't have that.

10:44.368 --> 10:47.036
Mom would get it for me.

10:47.137 --> 10:49.772
Her name is Evelyn.
<i>Evelyn.</i>

10:49.873 --> 10:51.641
It's a very simple combination
of the words

10:51.742 --> 10:53.743
"evil" and "villain."

10:53.844 --> 10:57.814
Mr. Powell, lovely to see you.
And who's your little guest?

10:57.915 --> 11:00.550
This is Deion, my...

11:00.651 --> 11:02.151
foster child.

11:02.252 --> 11:03.786
Oh, I-I know children
aren't allowed

11:03.887 --> 11:05.167
in the dining room, but...

11:05.255 --> 11:06.622
No, it's not a problem.

11:06.724 --> 11:07.990
I think what you're doing
is wonderful.

11:08.092 --> 11:09.258
And what am I doing, exactly?

11:09.359 --> 11:11.127
Well, becoming a foster parent.

11:11.228 --> 11:12.662
Last year, my husband and I

11:12.763 --> 11:14.597
adopted a baby girl
from Vietnam.

11:14.698 --> 11:16.299
How liberal of you.

11:16.400 --> 11:18.334
Well, I hope we'll be seeing
more of you

11:18.435 --> 11:20.002
and your beautiful family.

11:20.104 --> 11:22.872
Lunch is on the house today.
Well, thank you.

11:24.908 --> 11:26.743
Do you think it's possible
you could scare up

11:26.844 --> 11:28.077
some chocolate milk for Deion?

11:28.178 --> 11:29.579
Of course.

11:29.680 --> 11:30.780
And if there's anything else
I can do,

11:30.881 --> 11:32.048
please, just let me know.

11:32.149 --> 11:35.284
Oh, how about a tee time?

11:35.385 --> 11:37.920
Oh, I'll have them
squeeze you in.

11:40.457 --> 11:42.058
Well, that was unexpected.

11:42.159 --> 11:45.094
Not really.
White people love me.

11:45.195 --> 11:47.930
Oh! Is this your little boy?

11:48.031 --> 11:49.999
Oh, he's adorable!

11:50.100 --> 11:52.540
Yeah, I suppose
he gets that from me.

12:02.913 --> 12:05.915
Oh, my God, Olivia.
What are you doing here?

12:06.016 --> 12:08.284
I let myself in. You really
should lock your doors.

12:08.385 --> 12:10.253
There are a lot of nut jobs
out there.

12:10.354 --> 12:13.289
Yeah, I was just thinking
the same thing.

12:13.390 --> 12:14.957
How long has it been?

12:15.058 --> 12:16.292
A while!

12:16.393 --> 12:18.895
I was still working
for Michael and Taylor.

12:18.996 --> 12:20.930
You were stalking them.

12:21.031 --> 12:23.666
I'm afraid I was a bit
unstable back then.

12:23.767 --> 12:26.169
But I can assure you,
I am perfectly sane now.

12:26.270 --> 12:27.904
Yeah...

12:28.005 --> 12:29.305
Have you spoken to Taylor?
I heard about the breakup.

12:29.406 --> 12:30.773
So sad.

12:30.874 --> 12:32.708
You don't look sad.

12:32.810 --> 12:35.578
Anyway, I'm here because
I'm looking to hire a new maid.

12:35.679 --> 12:38.948
Sorry, I don't have anyone...
for you.

12:39.049 --> 12:41.250
Oh, no. I'm not looking to use
your little agency.

12:41.351 --> 12:42.885
I've actually found the maid.

12:42.986 --> 12:44.921
I just need a reference
for Jesse Morgan.

12:45.022 --> 12:47.657
Jesse wants to work for you?

12:47.758 --> 12:49.992
Well, I hated
my last cleaning lady,

12:50.093 --> 12:51.894
so I thought I'd try
a cleaning <i> man.</i>

12:51.995 --> 12:53.296
Is he any good?

12:53.397 --> 12:57.066
Uh... well, uh...

12:57.167 --> 12:59.035
<i>Oh,</i> dear. That bad, huh?

12:59.136 --> 13:02.905
No, no, Jesse's...
He's great.

13:03.006 --> 13:05.641
I'm just not sure that <i> you</i>
would be a good fit for him.

13:07.211 --> 13:09.771
Because I'm such
a perfectionist.

13:11.648 --> 13:13.849
Thank you for your candor,
Marisol.

13:15.853 --> 13:18.120
I miss this.

13:18.222 --> 13:20.690
We should do it again sometime.

13:20.791 --> 13:23.059
Definitely.

13:24.328 --> 13:25.895
What are you doing?

13:25.996 --> 13:28.064
I'm cleaning the chandelier.

13:28.165 --> 13:30.933
You took it down
from the ceiling?

13:31.034 --> 13:33.903
Well, don't worry.
I'll put it back.

13:34.004 --> 13:35.171
But I dusted it yesterday.

13:35.272 --> 13:36.706
You don't have to go
to all the trouble.

13:36.807 --> 13:37.907
Oh, I don't mind.

13:38.008 --> 13:39.408
I'm just giving it
a good scrubbing.

13:39.443 --> 13:42.345
I told you, I am trying
to impress Dr. Neff.

13:42.446 --> 13:45.781
But I can't do that if you
keep one-upping me.

13:46.437 --> 13:50.139
I don't believe in
doing things halfway so...

13:50.240 --> 13:52.760
But everything you're doing
goes against "Maid Code."

13:52.843 --> 13:54.677
- What's that?
- Maids have an understanding.

13:54.778 --> 13:57.138
We've got each other's backs.

13:57.181 --> 14:00.783
Sometimes you let me shine,
sometimes I let you shine...

14:00.884 --> 14:03.352
Okay, first, I don't think
"Maid Code" is a thing,

14:03.454 --> 14:04.587
and I intend to ask around.

14:04.688 --> 14:06.422
And second,
I refuse to do bad job

14:06.523 --> 14:08.224
just because you can't keep up.

14:08.325 --> 14:12.195
But you're supposed to be
helping me while I'm pregnant.

14:12.296 --> 14:14.376
Well, the truth is, if you
want to impress Dr. Neff,

14:14.398 --> 14:16.833
try being more...

14:16.934 --> 14:19.302
impressive.

14:19.403 --> 14:21.871
