- You <i> what?</i>
- I was dusting,

30:45.462 --> 30:49.098
and Joy told me not to touch it,
but I thought I knew better.

30:49.199 --> 30:53.602
For God's sake, Zoila,
this was my mother.

30:53.703 --> 30:55.070
It still is...

30:55.172 --> 30:56.505
mostly.

30:56.606 --> 30:59.208
You can rest assured,

30:59.309 --> 31:01.310
Genevieve is gonna hear
about this.

31:01.411 --> 31:02.878
I understand.

31:06.283 --> 31:08.250
You took the blame for me.

31:08.351 --> 31:12.855
Like I said, Maid Code.
We got each other's back.

31:17.894 --> 31:19.361
But just so you know,

31:19.462 --> 31:22.097
Spence and I are not having
an affair.

31:22.199 --> 31:25.267
Did he tell you to say that?

31:25.368 --> 31:27.469
No.

31:27.571 --> 31:30.706
It's the truth.

31:32.876 --> 31:38.047
We're in an addiction
support group together.

31:38.148 --> 31:43.719
Before you started working here,
I had an overdose.

31:43.820 --> 31:46.155
I was taking
some prescription pills.

31:46.256 --> 31:48.023
I thought that
that was an accident.

31:48.124 --> 31:50.226
It was, but it was also
a wake-up call.

31:50.327 --> 31:53.128
I realized that I'd become
dependent on those pills.

31:53.230 --> 31:57.700
I was using them as a crutch.
So I decided to get help.

31:57.801 --> 31:59.635
I started going to meetings.

31:59.736 --> 32:02.204
Uh, Spence was
in the same group.

32:02.305 --> 32:05.307
I already knew him, so I
asked him to be my sponsor.

32:05.408 --> 32:08.210
He's been helping me
get my life back together.

32:08.311 --> 32:10.412
So then how come
you slapped him?

32:10.513 --> 32:14.216
With you working here, he felt
it was getting too complicated.

32:14.317 --> 32:16.652
He told me he can't
sponsor me anymore.

32:16.753 --> 32:18.187
Oh, my gosh.

32:18.288 --> 32:20.089
I-I guess I just...
I snapped.

32:20.190 --> 32:21.457
Michael had just left me.

32:21.558 --> 32:24.093
It felt like spence was
abandoning me, too.

32:24.194 --> 32:26.161
I wish he would've
just told me.

32:26.263 --> 32:27.663
He couldn't.

32:27.764 --> 32:31.500
The support group is anonymous.
He was protecting me.

32:31.601 --> 32:34.470
He's a good guy, Rosie.

32:35.772 --> 32:37.673
You're lucky to have him
in your life.

32:46.616 --> 32:48.651
Go away.

32:51.688 --> 32:55.024
<i>Mon coeur,</i> I saw the show.

32:55.125 --> 32:56.525
I'm so, so sorry.

32:58.395 --> 33:00.529
My life is ruined.

33:00.630 --> 33:04.233
You think Jacklyn is going
to work with me now?

33:04.334 --> 33:06.068
I have nothing.

33:06.169 --> 33:07.569
You have me.

33:07.671 --> 33:10.031
Jacklyn wants a divorce.
We don't have to hide anymore.

33:10.106 --> 33:11.774
Maybe that's the silver lining.

33:11.875 --> 33:14.156
Sebastien, this relationship
was a mistake.

33:14.244 --> 33:15.477
How could you say that

33:15.578 --> 33:17.796
after everything we've done
to be together?

33:17.797 --> 33:19.197
What have we done?!

33:19.215 --> 33:22.618
We cheated on your wife.
We lied to her. We used her.

33:22.719 --> 33:24.486
We were horrible!

33:24.587 --> 33:26.588
You're upset.
You're not thinking clearly.

33:26.690 --> 33:29.625
I'm thinking clearly for
the first time in forever.

33:29.726 --> 33:31.794
I hate who I am
when I'm with you.

33:31.895 --> 33:35.164
<i>Mon coeur...</i>

33:35.265 --> 33:36.732
I need you.

33:36.833 --> 33:41.103
No, Sebastien.

33:41.204 --> 33:42.571
It's over.

34:03.426 --> 34:04.994
What happened?

34:05.095 --> 34:09.598
Well, we opened a lovely bottle
of Bordeaux.

34:09.699 --> 34:12.467
You had three glasses
and got a little tipsy.

34:12.569 --> 34:16.472
And we thought it best
if you slept it off.

34:16.572 --> 34:18.107
You don't remember?

34:18.208 --> 34:20.309
No.

34:20.409 --> 34:23.746
Because it never happened.
I don't drink!

34:25.782 --> 34:28.449
You people drugged me!

34:28.551 --> 34:29.717
That's ludicrous.

34:29.819 --> 34:31.520
Well, it'll be a cold day
in hell

34:31.621 --> 34:33.422
before I allow a child
to live here.

34:33.523 --> 34:35.123
What? Adrian!
Now just hold on.

34:35.225 --> 34:36.625
There must be something
we can do.

34:36.726 --> 34:38.527
Excuse me.
Yes, Deion.

34:38.628 --> 34:42.063
I took funny pictures of you.
Not now, sweetheart.

34:42.165 --> 34:44.733
No, no, look,
she was acting all weird.

34:49.406 --> 34:51.706
I think your boss would like
to see these pictures.

34:51.808 --> 34:54.143
Deion, give that to me.

34:54.244 --> 34:55.610
Not so fast.

34:55.712 --> 34:58.747
We'll keep them safe for you,

34:58.848 --> 35:04.119
provided Deion can remain
in our custody.

35:04.220 --> 35:08.323
Oh, my God! This little boy
is extorting me!

35:08.425 --> 35:09.625
I know.

35:09.726 --> 35:12.661
Turns out he's a Powell
after all.

35:16.171 --> 35:18.632
Taylor told you
about our support group?

35:21.023 --> 35:23.896
And I think you should
keep being her sponsor.

35:23.997 --> 35:25.664
She needs your help.

35:25.765 --> 35:29.501
Her marriage is over.
You can't leave her, too.

35:29.603 --> 35:31.670
You'd be okay with that?

35:31.771 --> 35:34.506
I'm sorry I got so angry.

35:34.608 --> 35:36.876
I guess thinking of you

35:36.977 --> 35:39.678
with another woman
still makes me crazy.

35:39.779 --> 35:43.949
Believe me, I understand.

35:45.719 --> 35:47.453
Which cheek did I slap?

35:47.554 --> 35:48.921
That one.

35:51.658 --> 35:52.938
Better?

35:54.895 --> 35:56.862
Well, Taylor slapped
the other one.

35:56.963 --> 35:59.365
That hurts, too.

36:13.446 --> 36:16.548
You're a great man,
Mr. Spence.

36:16.650 --> 36:19.285
You always do the right thing.

36:19.386 --> 36:21.620
Yeah.

36:21.721 --> 36:23.656
I hate that about me.

36:26.126 --> 36:29.495
Don't be a stranger, okay?

36:48.515 --> 36:51.517
Dr. Neff?

36:51.618 --> 36:54.853
Zoila feels really awful
about what happened.

36:56.890 --> 36:59.425
It's not just about the ashes.

36:59.526 --> 37:02.528
Ever since I moved in here,

37:02.629 --> 37:04.330
Zoila has been
trying to undermine

37:04.431 --> 37:05.864
my relationship with Genevieve.

37:05.966 --> 37:07.566
Oh, I don't know about that.

37:07.667 --> 37:08.934
Oh, I do.

37:09.035 --> 37:10.536
And sooner or later,

37:10.637 --> 37:13.439
Genevieve is going to have to
choose between us.

37:13.540 --> 37:16.575
And you are going to help her
make the right choice.

37:16.676 --> 37:18.043
I am?

37:18.144 --> 37:20.679
Yes.

37:20.780 --> 37:22.982
I'm counting on you, Joy.

37:26.920 --> 37:29.455
I'm sorry.
She ran right past me.

37:29.556 --> 37:32.825
It's okay, Thomas.

37:32.926 --> 37:35.394
I wanna hear
what she has to say.

37:37.664 --> 37:39.264
Well?

37:39.366 --> 37:41.767
I am so, so sorry.

37:41.868 --> 37:44.803
When I met Sebastien, I didn't
know how amazing you were.

37:47.507 --> 37:51.677
So it was okay to screw him
because you didn't know me?

37:51.778 --> 37:53.545
Look, I don't expect you
to forgive me,

37:53.646 --> 37:55.914
but I just wanted you to know
that I ended it with him.

37:56.016 --> 37:57.683
I don't...

37:57.784 --> 38:00.853
I don't care
about Sebastien anymore.

38:02.238 --> 38:04.594
But you wanna know
what hurts the most?

38:06.800 --> 38:09.041
I thought you and I
were friends.

38:09.076 --> 38:13.766
If it means anything, Jacklyn,
that part was real.

38:13.867 --> 38:16.735
It means nothing at all.

38:18.571 --> 38:20.806
Anyway...

38:20.907 --> 38:22.374
I completely understand

38:22.475 --> 38:24.576
why the label
would wanna drop me.

38:24.677 --> 38:26.545
Oh, we're not dropping you.

38:26.646 --> 38:29.615
What? You're still gonna
release my album?

38:29.716 --> 38:31.550
I didn't say that.

38:31.651 --> 38:33.485
I don't understand.

38:33.586 --> 38:36.989
We have you under
an exclusive contract.

38:37.090 --> 38:41.026
So your album is gonna sit
on a shelf and rot.

38:41.127 --> 38:43.362
<i>What?</i> You can't do that!

38:43.463 --> 38:44.897
Of course I can.

38:44.998 --> 38:48.934
You can't make music
anywhere else.

38:49.035 --> 38:50.969
I own you.

38:53.907 --> 38:56.375
So Mrs. Taylor
isn't having an affair.

38:56.476 --> 38:57.910
You were right.

38:58.011 --> 38:59.978
I've been thinking, and maybe
you were on to something.

39:00.080 --> 39:02.581
I spoke to Michael's ex,
Olivia,

39:02.682 --> 39:06.885
and she claims that she's been
seeing him behind Taylor's back.

39:06.986 --> 39:10.422
Maybe Blanca knew,
and that's why she was killed.

39:10.523 --> 39:11.890
Maybe.

39:11.991 --> 39:14.960
I can't imagine why Michael
would go back to Olivia.

39:15.061 --> 39:16.662
She's... certifiable.

39:16.763 --> 39:18.797
She could be making it up.

39:18.898 --> 39:21.600
- There's something else.
- Hmm?

39:21.701 --> 39:24.403
She said Blanca was murdered.

39:24.504 --> 39:27.439
But everyone thinks
Blanca killed herself.

39:27.540 --> 39:28.820
Except us.

39:28.875 --> 39:30.375
The killer knows the truth.

39:30.477 --> 39:33.512
You think Mr. Michael's ex-wife
murdered Blanca?

39:33.613 --> 39:36.281
If she did, she had help.
She couldn't do it alone.

39:36.382 --> 39:38.884
<i>Ay.</i> This is crazy.

39:38.985 --> 39:43.288
Yeah, well... so is Olivia.

39:43.389 --> 39:44.690
I just wanted to let you know

39:44.791 --> 39:46.558
that I'm sending you
the rest of your money.

39:46.659 --> 39:50.496
Everything's working out
just as I planned.

39:50.597 --> 39:53.398
No, no, you've done more than
enough for me.

39:53.500 --> 39:56.435
I'll take it from here.

